    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I just discovered this is probably just a misdirected error message in some cases. I get the error when using 2D arrays in my dict:\n\n``` python\nfoo = {'a':random.rand(10,1), 'b':random.rand(10,1)}\npd.DataFrame(foo)\n```\n\nThis raises the error stating: \"ValueError: If using all scalar values, you must pass an index\"\n\nHowever, if I flatten these arrays, everything works as expected:\n\n``` python\nfoo = {'a':random.rand(10,1).flatten(), 'b':random.rand(10,1).flatten()}\npd.DataFrame(foo)\n```\n\nSo, I think the error checking could be improved by distinguishing between scalar-only values and ndarray values.\n\nKeep up the good work!\n"
  },
